'''Amplify''' is a [[keyword ability]] on creatures that allows the player to reveal creature cards in their hand that share a creature [[subtype|type]] with the creature. The creature enters the [[battlefield]] with a number of [[+1/+1 counter]]s for each such card revealed. Some creatures with amplify have additional abilities tied to the number of +1/+1 counters on them (see <c>Kilnmouth Dragon</c>).

All tournament-legal creatures with Amplify were printed in ''[[Legions]]''.

==Rules==
{{CR+G}}

==Rulings==
*The player who will control the creature is the one who reveals the cards.
*Each revealed card must share a creature type with the card with amplify. The reminder text reminds you what those types are.
*Using the ''[[Onslaught]]'' card <c>Artificial Evolution</c> on a spell with amplify on the stack can change what types need to be revealed. The card <c>Conspiracy</c> can also change what types need to be revealed.
*If multiple creatures with amplify are entering the battlefield under your control at the same time, you may reveal the same cards for each of them.
*If you cast <c>Clone</c> (or a creature with a similar ability) and choose for it to copy a creature with amplify, you get to reveal cards and have the creature get +1/+1 counters.

